Recently, I had a dentist say I had 7!!!! Cavities. This didn‚Äôt make any sense because I take really good care of my teeth. Even though I hadn‚Äôt been to the dentist in a couple years, this didn‚Äôt seem right.

So my dad recommended I get a second opinion from Alex. I‚Äôm glad I did! It turned out the x rays the last dentist took were not good, and that upon another set of x rays and a visual exam I had just 1 cavity!

There‚Äôs a lot of BS in the dental industry, and you need a dentist you can trust to not over treat, and that‚Äôs why I‚Äôd recommend Alex.

The other things I love about the office is the friendly helpful staff, decor and overall vibe.  This is everything I want from the dental experience and that‚Äôs why I come here.

<Text>I had neglected my teeth for years.  The last time I visited a dentist was over four years ago and was guilty of irregular brushing and flossing.  I decided to search for a Dentist that I could call my primary and begin a new regiment of taking care of my teeth.

I found Doctor Alex Chaney and I was not disappointed.

What impressed me first from the Chaney & Chaney Dentistry website was the link to the beautiful artwork by Doctor Alex and innovative creations by Doctor Victor, his father.  It struck me that it would be brilliant to have a Dentist who was not only knowledgeable but also an Artist--for surely to obtain beautiful teeth would require the hands and eye of an artist so much as the knowledge of a doctor.  It also appealed to me to be a patron of a family business.

Doctor Alex's assistant Tamara was a delight from the moment I was called into the office.  With her radiant smile and personality, she was able to put my feelings of unease aside.  Very deftly and professionally, she obtained the required x-rays, in no time at all.

Doctor Alex told me he prides himself on being unjudgmental and kind--as well he should--for he indeed personifies these traits.  He is knowledgeable, patient, dapper and very interesting to talk to.  A lot of my fears were dispelled and my treatment was not as bad as I envisioned, (one cavity.)  What impressed me most  was that Doctor Alex was able to clean and treat my cavity all in one sitting!  There was no pain and I felt completely at ease with his confidant touch.

I left feeling like I had accomplished a lot all in one day!   I am grateful.

Thank you Doctor Alex!</Text><Time>1544160734123<//Time>< GmapID>

< text>
I just bought a new Alfa Romeo and needed another new car like a hole in the head.  My buddy just bought a Porsche 991 Carrera, and I had a very nice 997 which is the earlier model.  His purchase got my head reeling and I started looking. I saw this incredible 2015 dark blue GTS cabriolet at Future Auto Sales.

Truth be told I'm not too keen on any independent car dealerships in Los Angeles, and I was ready for some type of flim-flam or BS.  Call me skeptical.  Call me cantankerous.  But Arthur the owner was fabulous as were the salespeople including David.  I got a terrific trade in on my Porsche.  Normally I would never trade in my car, but they gave me a great price on the purchase and on the trade in.

They are even refinishing the lower skirt on the Porsche.  It wasn't a cheap purchase at over $100K and I want it to be perfect.

Great people.  As always YMMV.  My experience was super!

EDIT: I was in touch with Arthur shortly after I traded in my 2007 Porsche, and learned that it had a $1500 problem that COULD have been covered under my extended warranty had  I known about it. I felt horrible. The upshot is most dealers may have just sold the car with the problem as it was not easily detectable.  They did not.  I got more honesty and goodwill from these guys than I have from the two Porsche dealers I have done business with.<//text>

< UserId.>
114799247631855754766<//UserId.>
<name>Nasir Lawson< /name>< Date>
1603305512658< /Date>
<Rate>5<//Rate><Text>Would definitely recommend eating here. Great atmosphere, flavorful food, excellent customer service. Keep it up.</Text><pics>None< /pics>< Resp>
None</Resp>
<gmap_id>0x80c2bedec7e706ef:0x1e74b0e4e21185ff<//gmap_id></record></dataset><record>
< gmapID>
0x80c2bedec7e706ef:0x1e74b0e4e21185ff</gmapID>
< Review>
FOOD:  Premium Spicy Miso with Pork and Egg, Spam Musubi (munchies)
Once you get over the delicious aroma and the immaculate presentation, slurp up the goodness of the spicy miso!  The Miso is SPICY, which is fantastic if you can handle it.  Gosh, that Miso broth is to die for.  I felt tempted to take my remaining broth home to pour over my instant noodle packets for the next day.  Seriously, that good of Miso!  The noodles are just the right size, not too thick or thin and the pork was masterfully seasoned.  They add a soft boiled egg, which was not necessary and didn't add much to the already tasty dish.  If you've got the munchies, order the Spam Musubi.  They are the daintiest version of spam musubi I've tried, looking like a fancy hors d'oeuvre, but yummy nonetheless.

DESSERT:  Chibi toast
I had seen the beautiful pictures, but wasn't sure of the actual taste.  Literally tastes like deep fried, buttered french toast.  The toast comes with an assortment of fresh fruit (mango, strawberries, and kiwi) as well as matcha ice cream and whipped cream.  The dessert takes 20 minutes to prepare, so if you're interested, order with your entrees.  It is very different and I appreciate a change from creme br√ªl√©e or other generic desserts.

DRINKS:  Crystal Blue Lemonade and Honeydew Milk Tea
Both drinks are well made and served in cute mason jars.  If you're avoiding dairy, try the lemonade which is highly refreshing.  For my dairy drinkers, you can choose your milk tea with whole, regular, or silk milk and the honeydew is a nice touch.

ATMOSPHERE:  5 Stars
No sooner than we entered the restaurant, we were warmly greeted right away and got to choose any table.  The restaurant uses its limited space very wisely with a bench seat running against the wall and a long counter.  There are several tables in the middle and cute decorations.  Korean music videos in the background will keep you entertained while you wait for the food.

Yes, it's true, Hollywood offers a great deal of highly rated restaurants, but this place definitely is a serious contender!</Review>

<pics>None</pics><name>H Parrish<//name>< Rating>
5< /Rating>
</record></dataset><record>
<Gmap_id>0x80c2bedec7e706ef:0x1e74b0e4e21185ff</Gmap_id>< date>
1500327477817<//date>
< Text>
FOOD:  Premium Spicy Miso with Pork and Egg, Spam Musubi (munchies)
Once you get over the delicious aroma and the immaculate presentation, slurp up the goodness of the spicy miso!  The Miso is SPICY, which is fantastic if you can handle it.  Gosh, that Miso broth is to die for.  I felt tempted to take my remaining broth home to pour over my instant noodle packets for the next day.  Seriously, that good of Miso!  The noodles are just the right size, not too thick or thin and the pork was masterfully seasoned.  They add a soft boiled egg, which was not necessary and didn't add much to the already tasty dish.  If you've got the munchies, order the Spam Musubi.  They are the daintiest version of spam musubi I've tried, looking like a fancy hors d'oeuvre, but yummy nonetheless.

DESSERT:  Chibi toast
I had seen the beautiful pictures, but wasn't sure of the actual taste.  Literally tastes like deep fried, buttered french toast.  The toast comes with an assortment of fresh fruit (mango, strawberries, and kiwi) as well as matcha ice cream and whipped cream.  The dessert takes 20 minutes to prepare, so if you're interested, order with your entrees.  It is very different and I appreciate a change from creme br√ªl√©e or other generic desserts.

DRINKS:  Crystal Blue Lemonade and Honeydew Milk Tea
Both drinks are well made and served in cute mason jars.  If you're avoiding dairy, try the lemonade which is highly refreshing.  For my dairy drinkers, you can choose your milk tea with whole, regular, or silk milk and the honeydew is a nice touch.

ATMOSPHERE:  5 Stars
No sooner than we entered the restaurant, we were warmly greeted right away and got to choose any table.  The restaurant uses its limited space very wisely with a bench seat running against the wall and a long counter.  There are several tables in the middle and cute decorations.  Korean music videos in the background will keep you entertained while you wait for the food.

Yes, it's true, Hollywood offers a great deal of highly rated restaurants, but this place definitely is a serious contender!<//Text>

<text>Prices went way up portions went WAY down!!! I don't usually notice things like that, but damn.

My delivery ramen is 3/4 the amount as it used to be. They don't even fill up the broth in the small container while charging $3 more than they used to.I love Chibiscus. It's my little hole in the wall neighborhood ramen spot. The ramen is of the best in LA (top 3 and I've had it all over) and because it's a little tucked away you can usually get seated right away and the piping hot ramen will come pretty quickly.

Great for vegetarians (seriously they have a veggie bun that was so good my girlfriend had to make sure it wasn't real meat).

My only complaint is that it is pretty small, you'll feel like you're in conversation with the strangers next to you. And there's something about ramen that just doesn't hold well for take out so you're sort of forced to come in, but like I said... it's well worth it!</text>< Pics>

< review>
There are a bunch of Ramen joints popping up in this area, and after loving the place across the street until they changed owners, we found this place. IT is the best one, the selection, the richness of the broth, and all the other little bites they offer including bubble milk teas and such. Service is also great. Nom Nom Nom! Couple things to note: it is a small place so i imagine it could get packed at peak times, we always try to avoid that, so we have never had a problem, also, parking may be an issue the lot in from serves quite a few stores and is usually full.</review>

Wow super unimpressed. Over hyped. Restaurant is tiny so with very limited seating. Service was okay.

We ordered tonkatsu Ramen, spam masubi, kimchi fried rice, and a lemonade. My favorite thing we ordered was the lemonade. It was refreshing, light, and a little sweeter than it was bitter. The Ramen was eh OK. There are so many other Ramen places; the Ramen here doesn't even compare. The spam masubi was abysmal. The spam to rice ratio way off in favor of the rice with the rice falling off. The rice was loosely packed making it difficult to eat. The spam was burnt. The size was awkward. The sauce was missing something. The kimchi fried was decent and almost close to one you could get in ktown.

Will I come back....? Hm, maybe... to try the desserts.</text>

<rating>5<//rating><userid>111883937232289129288</userid><Response>None< /Response>< date>

< userid>
115563457627389021310<//userid>
<Name>Juvi Guevara</Name>< Time>
1435704597929< /Time>
<Rate>5</Rate>< review>
This tiny, unassuming, yet cute Asian restaurant offers some pretty unique dishes you might only ever find in a Japanese anime and the vibe positively screams K-Drama, complete with Asian music videos playing on the TV. The menu is modest, but packed with enough flavor and uniqueness that you'd be hard-pressed to find something you don't absolutely want to try at least once.

Being an avid anime lover and Korean Drama watcher myself, (don't tell anyone), there are a few things on the menu I've always wanted to try but have never found anywhere else, such as the famous Japanese OmuRice, which is a soft, fluffy omelet served with fried rice & ketchup. It's... interesting; definitely on the sweet-savory side, and so packed with protein & carbs, this meal practically pays for itself. It's good. Try it.

Their Kimichi Fried Rice is also really popular- It comes with your choice of meat, chicken, or mushrooms, and packs a hell of a lot of flavor from the fermented cabbage. If you love kimichi, this beast is for you.

It being an Asian joint- totally not being racist here- you know the desserts will be taken to the next level. Their Bread Pudding, served with vanilla bean ice cream, just made Yelp's list of best Bread Puddings in LA. It's a meal in & of itself, but definitely worth splurging on the calories. It takes decadence to the next level. Forget the food, and just eat this if you have to. It's worth it.

The rest of what they offer is great, too, but first-timers should really go for the local favorite, and that OmuRice is something else. The ramen- also good. Whatever you choose, it will be oishii! That means "delicious" for you non-anime watchers, out there.</review>

<Text>This is a cute place in Hollywood that offers ramen, Asian snacks, drinks and desserts. :)

AMBIANCE:
Casual. They have about 6-8 tables and a few barstool seats.

SERVICE:
Nice, friendly service.

DRINK:
*Green milk tea - Good! I liked the flavor of the tea. Not the best that I've had but it's nice to be able to complement my ramen with milk tea.

FOOD:
*Spicy Miso Ramen - Tasty! I liked the flavor of the broth. The slices of pork were nicely cut and had a good flavor. The ramen was also done well.

PARKING:
Small parking lot. Yay for free parking! If there's no spaces, they have meters on the street that are free after 6pm.

If I'm ever in the area, I would come back again. :)< /Text>< pics>

<userid>102918253898437847981</userid><username>Rodney S< /username><Date>1415643493642< /Date><Rate>4< /Rate>< review>
Chinensis? Shybiscuits?  Kidiscus?

Chibiscus is an Asian Fusion restaurant that's quaint (code for tiny) with free parking in a small private lot.  In LA?  That's unheard of!

After a fun & exhausting day touring LA, we needed to fuel up our bodies with some nourishment.  A quick phone search later & Chibiscus became our next destination.

I haven't had ramen in awhile, so my order was the Chibiscus Tonkatsu Ramen.
After a short wait, I had my hot bowl of ramen in hand.  Thick, delicious broth with a perfectly cooked egg.  Noodles just the right consistency.  The pork slices were tender & I slurped my soup down to the very last drop.

My friends let me have some of their Kimchi Fried Rice.
A good sized portion with a runny egg on top, the dish was a little salty for me.  This coming from a guy that usually tolerates things on the salty side.  Great flavor, though.

If you're looking for something sweet, various boba teas/smoothies/lemonades are available at your leisure, with some being organic.

Service was good.  Our waters were refilled timely, and we had our food within a reasonable amount of time.  Seating is minimal, with maybe enough for 20 or so.  As previously stated, parking is free if it's available.  Anyone that knows me, knows I hate having to pay for parking.

We all left with happy bellies

Chibiscus, I enjoyed dining at your establishment.  The ramen was on point, with good service and competitive prices.  Matter of fact, all this ramen talk is making me feen for it now.  Slurp!

Highly recommend!
NOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNOMNO< /review>

Maria Stevens</name>
< time>
1575998909565</time>
<Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
I eat here once in a while. Today I had two shrimp tacos and (my Favorite) two al pastor tacos. As always, chips are gratis, and the salsa bar is outstanding. I always order the tacos here, because they are the most-authentic street tacos I have found in this area. They have it all, including cabeza, lengua, and buche; not to mention the usual asada, al pastor, pollo, and carnitas. Although I almost always order the tacos, they also make a killer burrito. If you love Mexican food, you have to try Taqueria Guerrero.</Review>

Been coming to guerreros for years as a visitor to Santa Maria, always enjoying the variety of food and drinks here. My most recent visit had me order the Al pastor tacos and my guest some lengua tacos. <Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
After some very bad experiences, and being new to the L.A. area, I wasn't sure which vet I could trust with my tiny 10-year-old chihuahua. Last year she ended up needing several extractions, and I really didn't want her to lose any more teeth or undergo anesthesia. It's hard to know which vets are more cost-conscious than caring, and which ones are more eager to pull teeth than to save them. I am so glad I called this Banfield location! Dr. Taylor was professional and thorough while examining my dog, and so kind and patient while explaining that a radiograph given during a dental cleaning would tell us whether the tooth root had periodontal disease, but that my dog didn't have enough plaque buildup to warrant a cleaning (and anesthesia) just yet. I was so impressed (and relieved!) with this attentive care that prioritized my dog's health.
The staff here is also excellent - kind on the phone, communicative and cheerful while you're waiting for your pet, and wonderful with nervous pets. My typically clingy, anxious chihuahua was surprisingly calm when they brought her back to me in a little blue Banfield bandana :) Princess has definitely found her new people!<//Review>

<review>This location is top notch. Friendly staff, easy check in and out, vets are great!

Been to many Banfield locations across the country during my travels and this one is one of the best.

Parking is super convenient in a supermarket plaza which makes running errands a breeze. Brought my pup in for a few issues and staff were speedy in getting us checked in for an early drop off appointment.

Nice clean lobby area with a beverage station and modest display of items for sale. Noticed the low price for pill pockets and picked those to as an added bonus this trip!

I've had the positive experience of meeting each of their vets and they are all very engaging and highly professional. Took great care of my older pup with a few issues and really made me feel like they did their best to ensure no services were unnecessary. They called me up to us me a few times and ask if I needed anything else looked into. Picked up my girl all happy and tail wagging from a great visit for both of us!

It was a great experience across the board. <rate>4<//rate>< Text>
The staff are super helpful, and the store is pretty clean and organized. Some tips for shopping here. Deliveries and returns have always been pretty easy and straight forward.
1. Always do some research first, they will price match to meet competition.
2. Don't pay sticker price, use promotions to get the best deal.
3. Always communicate with the staff, and try to haggle a deal if your on the fence about the purchase.

You should never pay full price, always look for the deals. Hope this helps!< /Text>

<Gmap_id>0x80851245b8b01dd1:0x656eca8e6787e1b5<//Gmap_id><user_id>103845509267917465799< /user_id><rating>5</rating>< text>
Went to Ashley shopping for a Sofa. My shopping ninja niece Susan discovered something  unique about Ashley. Ashley's in store prices ( even on sale) are higher than the prices for the same item at the independent  retailers that sell Ashley. However, the on line prices are far, far lower than either. The Ashley store will price match the Ashley online price. This gives you the opportunity to touch and see what you are considering  before you buy. Gives you local delivery and the opportunity to purchase their 5 year in-home damage/spill warranty at an incredibly  low price (as it is based on the price of the purchase). Because Ashley online was clearancing  the couch we selected, our out the door price at the local Store. with taxes,delivery and warranty  was 1/3  of the in store sale price.  I am dragging  my poor niece with me everywhere I go shopping now. Delivery was on time and professional<//text>

If I could post a negative 5 Star review for their follow up customer service, I would! My spouse and I bought a love seat from Ashley in Fairfield, approximately 1 1/2 months ago, which was delivered by two non-English individuals. They shoved it through the door, almost breaking it. We signed for it and they left. We inspected the love seat, after they left , and a flaw was found. We contacted Ashley and a technician/repair man was scheduled. We waited 2-3 weeks for him to come out because of scheduling difficulties. When the technician came out, he  indicated that they would order replacement parts and they would fix it in our living room. When asked what that meant, he said they would undo the back of the love seat pull it apart along with the front cushion and repair it. At that moment we said "No". We felt the extent of repair to this degree was unacceptable, and to have it done in our living room was definitely unacceptable. We purchased a new love seat not a damaged one. The technician said he would make that note (replace vs repair) and we should hear from Ashley within 7-10 days. We DID NOT hear from them! We waited 3 weeks and still never heard from them. I begin to make calls only to get the run around from their customer service department. I even called their corporate office, and the customer service person there was no help. Ashley does NOT stand behind their product and we had even purchased the EXTENDED Warranty. Apparently this too, was a waste of money. If you're looking for new furniture, rethink purchasing from Ashley.< /text>

Some things were destined to be together, such as peanut butter and jelly or the hard riffs of Tony Iommi paired with highly intoxicated vocals of Ozzy Osbourne. As fate would have it two more things came together in splendor that could only be conveyed through leather bound epics in the halls of Rivendale. As I traversed the boundless endtables and ottomans that fill a stadium sized warehouse known as Ashley Homestore, my gaze landed on a sight so glorious it could make a zealot out of the most stringent of non believers. The plush oversized cushions drew me in like Gollum it‚Äôs precious, and I crumbled onto it‚Äôs all encompassing embrace. Moments later my attention, for what it was worth, was drawn to a man with impeccable dress and pleasant demeanor. He talked extensively about quality of craftsmanship and value retention of such a magnificent piece of furniture. He called himself T.C. But from that day forth I shall call him brother. Money spent that day pales in comparison to the wealth this couch will give me in its life and mine.</Review>

<Review>(Translated by Google) To all Ashley Furniture clients, I want to express my horrible experience. I went with my husband to the store in fairfield in mid-September and bought a dinning set, the shipment was for Sep 21 for which my husband and I took the day off. When they arrive we see that they only brought the chairs and not the table, according to them, someone called me and I agreed that they would leave only the chairs without the table, which is totally a lie. As we did not receive them, I was calling to find another fast shipping date and they gave it to me until October 12, I accepted with the frustration that I had no dinning for my family.
Oct 12 arrives which I asked again for the day off. The table arrives and it was totally broken, my frustration and anger was so great that I decided to accept the chairs only, which I checked and I did not see anything broken, my husband arrives in the afternoon and turns the chairs upside down and two of They had broken legs and the other had a stain, we immediately went to the store and asked to speak to the manager (a hairless man not very nice) I explained my problem and demanded that he please cancel my entire order because it was so much my frustration and such poor customer service that I did not want to continue dealing with the store. To all this he told me that they could not cancel it because I had already accepted the chairs, so I had to reveal myself and mention that I was going to sue them. The manager dares to tell me that out of courtesy he was going to try to approve the cancellation but that he did not assure me anything ... very angry I returned to my house to wait for the call that they would make me in 7 days, they never called me and then obviously I had to call and They tell me that my case was approved and that on October 25 they would pick up the chairs and give me my refund ...
I asked for the day off for the third time and on October 25 and I see that they are bringing the table again and there is no order to pick up the bad chairs that they left me, and if they take them without an order, it is most likely that They will charge me, I still have the chairs in my garage and my husband is dealing with this situation that I do not know where it will end .....
I have never in my life shopped at that store again with such poor quality and worst customer service.
